<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 12 at 6:47PM MDT until July 12 at 7:15PM MDT by NWS Boulder</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 715 PM MDT
FOR CENTRAL LOGAN COUNTY...
At 647 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Fleming, or 17
miles east of Sterling, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees. Hail damage to
vehicles is expected.
This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
central Logan County.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
